For a magical 80 minutes Lowvelders forgot their differences and stood behind Siya Kolisi and his Springbok team when they took on the English on Saturday in the 2019 Rugby World Cup final in Yokohama, Japan. With 57 million supporters behind them, the Springboks soared to victory, bringing new hope to a divided nation. Here is how Lowvelders supported them, in videos sent in by our readers:  